Limpopo cops have arrested 1098 suspects during the
multi-disciplinary and intelligence driven joint operations that were conducted
in all the crime infested areas of the province. The operations lasted until on Monday morning, 23 April. Limpopo police spokesman Lieutenant Colonel Moatshe
Ngoepe said these operations composed of various police units. "They Â were
conducted in a concerted effort to uproot and deal with the common generators
of crime and crime tendencies in all the policing Clusters and will continue to
spark dust along the streets, roads, residential places, farms and businesses
until crime is normalised. "These operations included road blocks, stop and
searches, patrols, tracing of wanted suspects, raiding of illegal business and
inspections of firearm dealers," said Ngoepe. The arrested suspects have started appearing before
different Magistrate Courts throughout the Province.